-- MBIA Surges After Report Insurer Settled with Bank of America
-- B y   M a r y   C h i l d s
-- 2013-05-06T16:34:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-06/mbia-surges-after-report-insurer-settled-with-bank-of-america.html
MBIA Inc. (MBI)  surged as much as 57 percent
after Dow Jones Newswires reported Bank of America Corp. will
pay $1.6 billion of cash as part of a settlement with the bond
insurer of mortgage-bond litigation.  MBIA was up  43 percent  to $14.10 at 12:25 p.m. in New York
after earlier climbing to as high as $15.45. The intraday jump
is the most ever.  The settlement includes a $500 million line of credit, Dow
Jones reported today, citing people familiar with the matter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
